article.headline: Miss. Valley St. 67, Jackson State 54
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Edward Mack scored 21 points and Attarrius Norwood added 20 as Mississippi Valley State swept Jackson State for the season with a 67-54 win on Saturday night. The Delta Devils (20-6, 14-2 Southwestern Athletic Conference) won its seventh straight game despite 6-for-32 shooting in the first half. Jackson State (10-14, 8-7) lost its fourth straight game. The Tigers committed 18 turnovers and shot 39 percent. Ishmael Joyce led the Tigers with 18 points. Mississippi Valley State broke a 24-24 halftime tie by going on a 10-2 run in the first three minutes of the second half. The Delta Devils never trailed again. Mississippi Valley State, who beat the Tigers earlier this season in Itta Bena, shot 54 percent in the second half and led by as many as 15 points late in the game. Hosea Butler added 14 points for Mississippi Valley.
